<h3><b style="">Step 1: Discuss </b><b style="">Concerns<o:p></o:p></b></h3></A>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 0.5in;">Before we can determine how to best
improve the transportation system, we need to know what the problems are. There
are two parts of this step:<span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0);"></span></p>


<ul><li><a style=""><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""></span></span><b>1a Brainstorm</b>: </a></li><ul><li><a style="">Participants&nbsp;</a><span class="MsoCommentReference"><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><span style=""></span></span></span>brainstorm and “tag” concerns about the
transportation system.</li></ul></ul>



<ul>
  <li><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""></span></span><b>1b Review Summaries</b>
  </li>
  <ul><li>The
moderator identifies themes among these concerns and writes a preliminary
summary synthesis of each theme.<br></li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span>Participants
review and discuss the synthesis, and suggest revisions.</li><li>The moderator revises themes to reflect participant suggestions, as appropriate.
  <br>
  <br>
</li></ul></ul>










<a name="step2"><h3><b style="">Step 2: Review Criteria<o:p></o:p></b></h3></a>



<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 0.5in;">Criteria are used to evaluate which
proposed transportation projects are best suited to address problems with our
current transportation system. Researchers identified a list of criteria before this process began, so that data relevant to these criteria could be gathered in advance of the decision process.</p>


<ul><li><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Wingdings;"><span style=""></span></span><b>2a Review Criteria</b></li><ul><li><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">
</span></span></span>Particip<!--[endif]-->ants review and discuss criteria in order to evaluate
how adequately they reflect each concern theme.</li></ul></ul>












<ul><li><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Wingdings;"><span style=""></span></span><b>2b Weigh Criteria</b></li><ul><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">
</span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Participants individually choose their favorite
criteria and weigh the relative importance of these criteria for project evaluation.<br>
<br></li></ul></ul>








<a name="step3"><h3><b style="">Step 3: Create Packages</b></h3></a><blockquote>In this step participants review proposed road and transit projects for improving the regional transportation system, and then create their own personal transportation improvement "package". A "transportation package" is simply a set of transportation projects
and sources of money to pay for those projects. Decision makers often
create packages as options to simplify regional transportation
improvement financing decisions.

</blockquote>



<ul><li><b>Step 3A: Review Projects</b><br>Prior to this decision process, a panel of transportation specialists have evaluated
each of the proposed projects and assigned them with scores for each criterion. <br></li><ul><li>Participants review a map of proposed road and transit projects.<br></li><li>Participants review information about projects of interest as well as project scores.</li><li>Participants discuss the appropriateness of project scores and the relative importance of different projects and project alternatives.<br></li></ul></ul>

<ul><li><b>Step 3b: Select Funding Options<br>
</b>Here you can read about available funding sources and
express their preferences for how funds should be raised to fund a
transportation improvment project.</li><ul><li>Participants review descriptions of funding sources</li><li>Participants select prefered funding options and see how much money these
options would raise. The participant can also see how much money these
options would cost him/her per year.<br>
    </li><li>Participant can select a maximum amount per year he/she is willing to spend in additional taxes.<br>
    </li></ul></ul>
<ul>
  <li><b>Step 3c: Create Personal Transportation Package<br></b>Based on the your prefered criteria weights and
prefered funding options, a suggested transportation improvment
package is displayed. Here you can revise this suggested package
to create your own personal transportation package.<br>
<br>
  </li>
  </ul>
<a name="step4"><h3><b style="">Step 4: Evaluate Packages</b><span class="MsoCommentReference"><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!--[if !supportAnnotations]--><span style=""></span></span></span><b style=""><o:p></o:p></b></h3></a>




<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 0.5in;">In order to simplify the decision process, we need to narrow down the number of different packages considered. Therefore, based on participant responses in Step 3, five new packages are
automatically constructed. These packages will represent the
diversity of participant preferences in terms of both project selection as well
as funding source selection. In this step participants evaluate the five new packages and
determine which one(s) to collectively endorse.</p>


<ul><li><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Wingdings;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">&nbsp; 
</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><b>4a Review Packages</b></li></ul>


<blockquote>
  <ul><li>Participants can read a brief overview of the
processes by which the 5 candidate packages were created.<br>
<!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span><span class="q" id="q_10cc6d99f0e54d4f_2"></span></li><li><span class="q" id="q_10cc6d99f0e54d4f_2">Participants review information about each individual package.<br>
</span></li><li>Participants discuss the relative benefits and drawbacks of individual packages.<br>
    </li></ul>
</blockquote>






<ul>
  <li><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Wingdings;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">
</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><b>4b Compare Packages<o:p></o:p></b></li></ul>





<blockquote>
  <ul><li>Participants use a variety of different tools for comparing the benefits and drawbacks of the five packages, such as cost, spatial equity, and overall scores for each of the criteria.</li><li>Participants can adjust their criteria weights to see how each package measures up based on their personal weighting choices. They can also compare the ranking of packages based on their own criteria weights to the aggregate criteria weights of all participants.</li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">&nbsp;</span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Participants discuss the potential benefits and
drawbacks of the different packages.</li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Participants discuss whether or not they wish to
collectively endorse the top-ranked package.<span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span></li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span><!--[endif]-->The moderator&nbsp; periodically polls participants to measure&nbsp; the degree to which a consensus is emerging regarding which package to collectively endorse. <span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span></li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span><!--[endif]-->At a designated time, all participants are asked to vote to endorse the package currently enjoying the majority of support.<span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Dissenting voters discuss whether or not they
wish to include a minority endorsement in the group report. If yes, then they
vote on which package to endorse</li>
  </ul></blockquote>

<a name="step5"><h3><b style="">Step 5: Prepare Group
Report<o:p></o:p></b></h3></a><blockquote>The final step is to compose a report about the results of this
decision process which will be delivered to transportation decision makers. <br><ul><li>The moderator creates a first draft and notifies participants when it is ready.<br></li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Participants
review and discuss this draft report and submit their comments and suggested
revisions.<span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span></li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span><!--[endif]-->The
moderator makes revisions and includes participant comments when appropriate.<span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span></li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Participants
review the final report.<span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span></li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;"><span style=""><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"></span></span></span><!--[endif]-->All
participants vote on whether to approve or disapprove the report. If majority
approve the report is forwarded on to decision makers. (Results of this final
vote will be included in the report sent on to decision makers.)</li></ul></blockquote>

